  "prompt": "Whats are stealth aircrafts?",
  "response": "Stealth aircraft are military aircraft designed to be difficult to detect by radar, infrared, sonar, and other detection methods. Key characteristics include:\n\n1. Design features:\n- Angular, faceted shapes that reflect radar signals away from receivers\n- Special radar-absorbing materials (RAM)\n- Reduced radar cross-section\n- Minimal exposed metal surfaces\n\n2. Purpose:\n- Avoid enemy detection\n- Penetrate enemy air defenses\n- Conduct reconnaissance or strike missions\n\n3. Notable stealth aircraft examples:\n- F-117 Nighthawk (first operational stealth aircraft)\n- B-2 Spirit bomber\n- F-22 Raptor fighter\n- F-35 Lightning II\n- B-21 Raider (newest stealth bomber)\n\n4. Advantages:\n- Reduced risk of detection\n- Increased survivability\n- Ability to operate in high-threat environments\n\n5. Technologies used:\n- Special surface coatings\n- Sophisticated shape engineering\n- Advanced materials\n- Reduced heat and sound signatures\n\nStealth technology continues to evolve, with countries investing heavily in developing more advanced stealth capabilities.",
